    "created_at": "2015-08-26T08:07:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-08-26T08:07:57Z",
    "body": "Sure, here's the result of a styled textarea and a raw one, this is what I got on the two tested Retina models:\n\n![screenflow](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/7288490/9488421/43d665be-4bda-11e5-9a68-f0aa3136b786.gif)\n\nAnd my html for this was:\n\n``` html\n<html>\n<head>\n  <title>Electron</title>\n  <style>\n    body {\n        background-color: #ECF2F5;\n    }\n    textarea.styled {\n        -webkit-appearance: none;\n        border: 1px solid #ced5d9;\n        color: #454a4c;\n        padding: 10px;\n        text-rendering: optimizeLegibility;\n        box-sizing: border-box;\n        line-height: 1.4;\n        resize: none;\n    }\n    textarea.styled:focus {\n        outline: none;\n        border-color: #00aaff;\n    }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <textarea class=\"styled\" placeholder=\"example placeholder\"></textarea>\n  <br>\n  <textarea placeholder=\"example placeholder\"></textarea>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n"
  },
